HEADWORD: makeshift
<hw>make"shift`</hw> <pr>(m⟦amac⟧k"sh⟦icr⟧ft`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>That with which one makes shift; a temporary expedient, with
implication of inferiority to the more usual object or means.</def>
<rj><au>James Mill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am not a model clergyman, only a decent
<qex>makeshift</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>G. Eliot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>make-up</ent>⟦br⟧
